        <comment>
  <id>109932476</id>
  <body><![CDATA[I wholeheartedly agree with your review, new updates included. I reread the series after the first hunger games movie came out. I'd enjoyed Mockingjay when the book was released; in fact, I sped through it that same night, so I don't think I processed it completely. Afterwards, when everyone was talking about how much Katniss's whining was dragging the book down, how depressing it was, etc., I wondered if I'd just overlooked big issues because I was just so happy to read the conclusion. <br /><br />But after that reread, I am still totally behind the book. I didn't exactly ENJOY the Katniss 'whining' (and maybe I skimmed a few parts of her internal monologues) but I completely understood WHY they were there, why she felt how she felt, and felt deeply satisfied with the ending (even her having children. I want to roll my eyes so hard when people get very upset she had kids after saying she didn't want them. Yes, some people will never change their stance on that topic, even if they decided at a young age, and that's fine. But Katniss ended up not being one of those people, and that is ALSO okay. Heaven forbid a young girl experiencing PTSD grow up, reexamine her feelings and realize she wants children with the man she loves now that the world she lives in is better.).]]></body>
  
